                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d544">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221 Dahl, Harold/74: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-11T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 11, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 11—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of October 8, 10 a.m.,<note n="8" xml:id="d544fn8">Not
                        printed.</note> Harold Dahl. General Queipo de Llano informed me this
                    morning that Dahl is <pb facs="0565" n="553" xml:id="pg_553"/> being exchanged
                    and that the exchange has probably already been effected. If it has not been
                    concluded he said it will take place immediately.<note n="9" xml:id="d544fn9"
                        >Dahl was never exchanged. He was finally released in February 1940 and
                        returned to the United States.</note> Repeated to Vigo and Ambassador
                    Bowers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
